The '''Zamorak Magical Institute''' (known as the '''Z.M.I.''') is a [[Zamorakian]] organisation which specialises in magics and [[runecraft]]. Formed after their banishment from the [[Order of Wizards]] following claims that they burned down the [[Wizards' Tower]],{{CiteNPC|npc=Archmage Sedridor|quote=The wizards who served Zamorak, the evil god of chaos, tried to claim our magical discoveries in his name. They failed, but in retaliation, they burnt the entire tower to the ground.}}{{CiteNPC|npc=Mage of Zamorak|quote=Naturally, they blamed the Zamorakians. Claimed we intentionally burnt the tower down. After the tower was rebuilt, we were banished from the Order of Wizards and forced underground.}} its main goal seems to be to arm Zamorakian magic specialists with runes and to gain access to the [[rune essence mine]],{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=Thanks to the portals, the Abyss has become a runecrafting gold mine, especially when combined with the pouches detailed previously. However, as also noted, lack of access to the lost Rune Essence Mine is preventing us from utilising the Abyss to its full potential.}} in which they believe that the Order has regained access to it.{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=One recent development of concern in this area is the sudden increase in rune production from the Order of Wizards. Could it be that they have found a way to the Rune Essence Mine themselves?}}

They have taken control of the [[Ourania Cave]] and the [[Ourania Altar|runic altar]] therein, and have access to a part of the [[Abyss]], where they have created rifts leading directly to temples housing the [[runic altar]]s.{{CiteText|text=Abyssal book|quote=While originally only intended as a way for us to access the Abyss, the portal spell soon proved to have some very beneficial side effects. It has also allowed us to open portals to most of the runic altars found across Gielinor.}} They seem to be active in the greater [[Varrock]] area. According to [[Savant]], the [[Temple Knight]]s suspect this organisation to be responsible for the burning of the Wizards' Tower in decades past and a number of other crimes.

